      <title>Hugo Notes</title>
      <link>https://saahilclaypool.github.io/notes/HugoNotes/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 14 Mar 2017 14:42:39 -0400</pubDate>
      <author>saahil@claypools.com (Saahil Claypool)</author>
      <guid>https://saahilclaypool.github.io/notes/HugoNotes/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;hugo-reference&#34;&gt;Hugo Reference&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/overview/introduction/&#34;&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt; is a static HTML Site generator. It takes directories of markdown and compiles them into linked HTML websites.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&#34;setup&#34;&gt;Setup&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Install Hugo&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;a)&lt;/strong&gt; Install the binary from apt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34;&gt;$ sudo apt install hugo 
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;b)&lt;/strong&gt; Install through &lt;a href=&#34;../GoNotes&#34;&gt;go&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34;&gt;$ go get -u -v github.com/spf13/hugo
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&#34;commands&#34;&gt;Commands&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create new content&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34;&gt; $ hugo new &amp;lt;path&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;thing&amp;gt;.md
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Serve Site Locally&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34;&gt;$ hugo server
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&#34;deploying-to-github&#34;&gt;Deploying to Github&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using this link: &lt;a href=&#34;http://gohugo.io/tutorials/github-pages-blog/&#34;&gt;http://gohugo.io/tutorials/github-pages-blog/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34;&gt;$ ./deploy.sh
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;h5 id=&#34;adding-theme&#34;&gt;Adding Theme&lt;/h5&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To get a theme, do git submodule add &lt;theme.git&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34;&gt;$ cd themes
$ git submodule add &amp;lt;Theme-URL&amp;gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;h5 id=&#34;cloning&#34;&gt;Cloning&lt;/h5&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To clone, submodules must also be cloned. To do this, use the following command&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34;&gt;$ git clone &amp;lt;url&amp;gt;  --recursive
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Or&lt;/em&gt; after cloning normally&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34;&gt;$ git submodule update themes (or other submodule directory)
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE&lt;/strong&gt; Must make a ssh key for the computer that is pushing to github.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://help.github.com/articles/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent/&#34;&gt;https://help.github.com/articles/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
